---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CapacityForecasterWidget from '../../features/capacity-forecaster/CapacityForecaster';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Technical Capacity Forecaster — Ethotechnics"
  description="Model compound decay against remediation tactics to see when teams saturate."
  mainClass="page page--wide"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section__header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Diagnostics</p>
      <h1>Technical Capacity Forecaster</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        Lightweight simulation for teams balancing stability, operational friction, and refusal windows. Use this tool when you
        need to stress-test delivery plans and export a PDF snapshot for stakeholders.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        <h2>Model assumptions</h2>
        <ul class="muted">
          <li>Baseline capacity declines unless remediation is scheduled.</li>
          <li>Refusal windows represent periods when teams pause new delivery.</li>
          <li>Forecasts compare “do nothing” vs. mitigation timelines.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="callout">
        <h2>Preview the output</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          You will export a PDF snapshot that compares baseline and remediated capacity over time.
        </p>
        <ul class="muted">
          <li>Inputs needed: baseline capacity, remediation timing, and refusal windows.</li>
          <li>Outputs include saturation callouts and stakeholder-ready notes.</li>
        </ul>
        <a
          class="button ghost"
          href="https://github.com/ethotechnics/et3/blob/main/docs/diagnostics-outputs.md#technical-capacity-forecaster"
        >
          View a sample PDF snapshot
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="muted">
        Modeling assumptions and inputs are documented in the
        <a href="https://github.com/ethotechnics/et3/blob/main/docs/diagnostics-capacity-forecaster.md">diagnostics
        guide</a>
        for contributors.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">Permanent link: <a href="/diagnostics/capacity-forecaster">/diagnostics/capacity-forecaster</a></p>
      <p class="muted">Exporting the results gives you a PDF summary to share with leadership or delivery partners.</p>
      <ol class="muted">
        <li>Set baseline capacity, delivery targets, and current operational friction.</li>
        <li>Schedule remediation timing and define any refusal windows.</li>
        <li>Run the simulation to compare baseline versus mitigated trajectories.</li>
        <li>Download the PDF snapshot for distribution and follow-up.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <CapacityForecasterWidget client:only="react" />
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
